description.narrative: (Cambodia): The Supporting Forests and Biodiversity project mitigates climate change and positively impacts biodiversity by improving governance and protecting targeted forests in Cambodia. With FY 2014 funds, activities will support community forestry groups pursue protection of their area, facilitate constructive dialogue between government and civil society, and increase equitable and sustainable income generation. The results will be reduced deforestation rates and greenhouse gas emissions; improved community management and governance of forests in partnership with the Cambodian government, civil society, and the private sector; and increased incomes for targeted groups. The project will play a supporting role in combatting wildlife trafficking through improved natural resource management and training activities. These results build on previous successes and will contribute to Cambodia's Enhancing Capacity for Low Emissions Development Strategy.
